## 4. Functional Zoning

- Entry/service zone: entrance vestibule, technical room, laundry/storage, guest bathroom, stair zone.
- Day zone: kitchen, dining, living room, fireplace zone, gallery lounge, terrace connections.
- Private zone: guest bedroom, master bedroom, bedrooms 2 and 3, walk-in closet.
- Sanitary zone: guest bathroom, master bathroom, bathroom 2.
- Outdoor zone: {{ terrace_zone_names }}.

## 5. Ground Floor Plan Narrative

- The ground floor is organized as the main arrival and social level.
- The entrance vestibule acts as a thermal buffer before the plan opens into kitchen, dining, living, fireplace, and terrace-facing zones.
- Service spaces are grouped to simplify future MEP coordination.
- The guest bedroom and guest bathroom support accessible guest use, subject to code and accessibility review.
- Ground floor configured room area: {{ ground_floor_area }} m2 across {{ ground_floor_rooms|length }} rooms.

## 6. Gallery Plan Narrative

- The gallery level contains the principal sleeping spaces and a secondary lounge overlooking or connecting visually to the main volume.
- Bedrooms are planned as compact sleeping rooms with natural ventilation and individual lighting/socket assumptions.
- Wet rooms on the gallery require careful plumbing, ventilation, acoustic, and waterproofing coordination.
- Gallery configured room area: {{ gallery_area }} m2 across {{ gallery_rooms|length }} rooms.

## 7. Terrace Design Narrative

