## 12. Material Palette

- Exterior: timber, stone, glass, standing seam metal roof.
- Interior floors: engineered wood, porcelain tile, sealed concrete or technical tile where appropriate.
- Interior walls: painted gypsum board, washable boards in service rooms, tile in wet zones.
- Ceilings: painted gypsum board, sloped board, exposed timber where appropriate.
- Terrace: exterior-rated decking, non-combustible cooking/fire zones, reinforced waterproof finishes where required.

## 13. Daylight and Views

- Primary daylight and view strategy centers on the living, dining, kitchen, gallery lounge, and terrace-facing rooms.
- Total configured window area from room data: {{ total_window_area }} m2.
- Window-to-floor ratios are planning indicators only and require architectural and energy review.
- Large view glazing must be coordinated with overheating, glare, privacy, bird safety, guard conditions, and structural openings.

## 14. Natural Ventilation Strategy

- Natural ventilation is assumed for most bedrooms and day spaces.
- Mechanical extract is assumed for wet rooms, laundry/storage, and technical spaces where configured.
- Stack-effect behavior around the stair/gallery zone must be reviewed for comfort, smoke movement, and winter operation.
- Final ventilation rates require mechanical engineering review.

## 15. Accessibility Considerations

- Ground floor guest bedroom and guest bathroom can support adaptable use, subject to dimensional and code review.
- Entrance, terrace thresholds, stair geometry, handrails, guards, and bathroom clearances require local accessibility review.
- This package does not certify accessibility compliance.

## 16. Fire Safety Concept Placeholders

- Fireplace zone requires fire-rated surround, hearth, flue, combustion air, clearance, and installation review.
- Sleeping areas require compliant egress, smoke/CO detection strategy, and fire separation review.
- Terrace fire pit and BBQ/outdoor kitchen are placeholders and require local fire-safety approval.
- This package does not certify fire-safety compliance.

